  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Chef has an integer array **X**, and a binary array **S**, both of size **N**. He wants to know how many vectors (denote by **V**) of **N** elements exist, for which the following conditions hold for all valid indices **i** (that is, for all 1 ≤ **i** ≤ **N**).\n\n\n0 ≤ **Vi** &lt; 1018If **Si** = 1, **Vi** is ≥ **Xi**, and if **Si** = 0, **Vi** ≤ **Xi**Sum of the elements of **V**, when viewed as a string, contains \"47\" as a substring.\n\n\nPlease help Chef find this count. Since it may be a very large number, you should output the count modulo **109+7**.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 ≤ **N** ≤ 8",
      "0 ≤ **Xi** &lt; 1018",
      "**Si** is either 0 or 1.",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "2",
      "0 22",
      "0 30",
      "**Output:**",
      "6",
      "Explanation:",
      "There are 6 such vectors: (17, 30), (18, 29), (19, 28), (20, 27), (21, 26), (22, 25)."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "**N****N****ith****Si****Xi****Si****Vi****Xi****Vi****Xi**",
    "outputFormat": "**109****7**",
